    "question": "Problem 2.11. Consider the reaction $1 + 2\\rightarrow 3 + 4$ . The lab frame is defined to be the one in which $\\underline{\\mathbf{P}}_2 = 0$ . The C.M. frame is defined to be the one in which $\\underline{\\mathbf{P}}_1^{\\mathbf{C.M.}} + \\underline{\\mathbf{P}}_2^{\\mathbf{C.M.}} = 0$ . Show that:(a) $\\mathbf{E}_{\\mathrm{total}}^{\\mathbf{C.M.}} = \\left(\\mathfrak{m}_1^2 +\\mathfrak{m}_2^2 +2\\mathfrak{m}_2\\mathbf{E}_1\\right)^{\\frac{1}{2}}",
